021-06-08T20:18:43Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Not yet sure if it would provide a remedy, but I have attributed a [fresh performance issue of git-annex](https://git-annex.branchable.com/bugs/significant_performance_regression_impacting_datal/#comment-4df4242f85746baef8afd32e0632c37c) (manifesting on OSX... may be shorter max cli size triggering it, didn't check) to a growth in how long `annex add` takes when we chop up our long list of files into separate `annex add` calls.  I think (didn't time) it should be faster if we just use a single `annex add --batch` process there.  This also reflects on  https://github.com/datalad/datalad/issues/4630#issuecomment-759854665 .  Given those observations, switching to `annex add --batch` could provide a notable performance benefit.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5721/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/5721/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}